<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;">The StraightFlo Valve is a <strong>drop in replacement for conventional reciprocating compressor valves</strong>. The <span style="color:rgb(98, 106, 113)">StraightFlo</span> brings to the industry <strong>a step improvement in performance, reliability and ease of service</strong>. Use of the StraightFlo Valve in your compressors will lead to reduced operating costs (reduced fuel consumption/reduced emissions), increased throughput, reduced downtime and reduced inventory.<br /><br />The StraightFlo Valve is a compressor reed valve that has a stainless steel seat and carrier with one or several modules or cartridges that are held stationary between them.<br />Each module is an enhanced reed valve that maximizes efficiency and reliability. All wear is contained in the module.<br />Since the modules do not move, there is no wear on the valve seat and carrier. Therefore, they never have to be machined or replaced over the life of the compressor.<br />There are a total of 8 modules in 3 materials that cover almost the entire reciprocating compressor application.<br />All modules have the same outside dimensions, but differ only in the lift and stiffness.<br />The correct module for an application is chosen by simulating the cylinder, valves, gas and operating conditions using Zahroof's Advanced Valve Simulation Program.<br />Irrespective of the size of the valve, 1.5" diameter to greater than 14" diameter, the same modules can be used. Larger valves simply have more modules.</div>


					
