<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><strong>The modules or inserts in the </strong><strong style="">StraightFlo valve are each enhanced reed valve modules, designed to be interchangeable, with very low flow losses and high reliability</strong>. There are 8 different modules in 3 materials to cover the entire reciprocating compressor application. The optimum module for an application is chosen using ZVI's Advanced Valve Simulation Program.<br /><br />Straight through flow path -- minimize valve losses.<br />Stainless steel reeds instead of moving/impacting/bending plastic plates and helical coil springs provide a step improvement in reliability. <br />High natural frequencies greater than 250Hz compared to 30Hz for poppets and 80Hz for plates solves pulsation and vibration related valve issues.<br />Design is highly tolerant to liquids and particles in the gas stream due to straight flow path, stainless steel reed design. Particles do not impact head on with hot plastic plate.<br />Excellent for multi-phase compression.<br />Reed lift and reed stiffness are optimized for a given application. Total of 8 combinations of lift and stiffness for all speeds (300 rpm to 3600 rpm), molecular weights, operating conditions.</div>


					
